# name:Mau
# internal_places_id: ded6804c7eee5cc286e6b0f862d57380d607bd0b
# places_reviews: {1: [], 2: [u"The worst pho I've ever had.\n\nWe ordered both beef and chicken pho. The chicken was very bland, essentially salty chicken broth that was also sweet. The beef broth was worse, very oddly seasoned, and again it was sweet. Service was nothing to write about, had to ask for water, refills etc."], 3: [], 4: [u'I like this place a lot. Good Vietnamese food in Mission District. Vibrant and buzzing ambiance + good service + great taste. Portions bare huge. Not much options for the vegetarians, but their Tofu Phone and Tofu Bun are amazing!'], 5: [u'Yummy soup. The appetizer rolls are quite nice. Great staff. Very nice atmosphere. Not a great area to wait for a table.', u'Great options for those that adhere to a gluten and dairy free diet. Phenomenal and helpful service is a huge plus. Ambiance was very nice too with good lighting and music that was not too loud. Pho and lemongrass chicken are some great gluten and dairy free options without sacrificing flavor or requiring special requests. Great restaurant in general and even better for those with allergies or intolerances. ', u'Great service and tasty food, although most dishes have been very salty in my 3 visits. Try the odd salads, pig ear was surprising good.']}
