# external_places_id: ChIJVVWVjGaAhYARH_4JjCTVBz8
# places_general_score: 4.1
# name:"Gott's Roadside"
# internal_places_id: 34e3cc5f52c03e5c267b255dd68c7776a72cde62
# places_reviews: {1: [], 2: [], 3: [], 4: [u"This was my first time eating at the Ferry Building, and Gott's was not a bad way to start. Lines here get ridiculously long during peak lunch hours, but just come before noon and you'll be fine. They have a great variety of choices on their menu. You'll find burgers, sandwiches, salads, tacos, fries, fish n chips, etc. Once you place your order at the front, you get a buzzer thing that will light up and vibrate when your food is ready. It took 15 min for my food to come out. A little on the slow side, but still bearable. They have a great outdoor seating area, and there's often live music playing nearby. Great vibe!\n\nAs for food, I got the Texas Burger (without jalapenos), and it was delicious! Loved the avocado and cheese combination, and the meat was cooked perfectly as well. Also got a side of garlic fries, and they were amazing!! Lots of good garlic flavor and the texture of the fries was perfect. Their ketchup is good too! All in all, I had a great experience here! Will definitely be back. Just not around peak lunch hour :)", u"Burgers were real and tasty. Beer was cold. Fast paced feel. Found the place a bit noisy but didn't out weigh the great food.  Nice to see your food prepared in front of you.  All the food was served on paper plates avid this worked.  Can see this would be a great place for a bite after work or Friday night dinner. We went Monday night and the place was busy still. All sorts of different people dining, people dining alone, families like us and groups of people out for a beer. Price was good for what you got. ", u"Enjoyed the vibe, lots of burger choices and good selection of draft beer. I didn't mind the slow service but for waiting, I expected a warmer burger and warmer fries. I'll certainly give them another shot, next time I'm in town", u"If you are wandering around the Embarcadero near the Ferry Building and are looking for a bite to eat, Gott's may be a good option. It's mainly about burgers and fries and stuff that goes with burgers and fries (salads, beer, shakes, ...). They have a lot of burger options and even have a pretty good veggie patty. They have both indoor and outdoor seating, mostly at long, shared tables. The line to order can get pretty long during the lunch rush, but it's pretty good if you have the time."], 5: [u'The food is amazing and great quality, there was a long wait but it was totally worth it! Outside seating is quite and nice if the weather is permitting! Totally recommend for a nice dinner or lunch if you can wait!']}
